com.percussion.design.objectstore
Class PSRelationshipConfig

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSComponent
      com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSRelationshipConfig
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSComponent, IPSCatalogIdentifier, IPSCatalogSummary, com.percussion.services.data.IPSCloneTuner, Serializable, Cloneable
public class PSRelationshipConfig
extends PSComponent
implements IPSCatalogSummary, com.percussion.services.data.IPSCloneTuner

This class represents objects conforming to the sys_RelationshipConfigLookup.dtd. The contents of RelationshipConfig elements are expanded using the sys_RelationshipConfig.dtd.

RS_NAMEDTRANSITION

public static String RS_NAMEDTRANSITION
Deprecated. we no more have built-in effects
This system property is used if rs_promote is enabled. It defines the transition to take for the original item if the new version becomes public. Defaults to 'Default', in which case the first transition in alpha order with the 'Default' flag set will be used to move the original item out of the current public state.

RS_FORCETRANSITION

public static String RS_FORCETRANSITION
Deprecated. we no more have built-in effects
This system property is used if rs_strongdependency is enabled. It specifies whether or not to transit strong dependents into a public state.

RS_ISLOCALDEPENDENCY

public static String RS_ISLOCALDEPENDENCY
This system property is used to determine if relationships of this type should be required to be packaged and deployed with the owner. Defaults to 'no', so that relationships are not by default required to be deployed with the owner.

PDU_INLINERELATIONSHIP

public static final String PDU_INLINERELATIONSHIP
One of the pre-defined user properties, to marks a relationship as an inline link relationship. The value of this property is the name of the field that contains the inline link plus the child row id delimited with a colon if this field belongs to a child editor. If this property is missing, null or empty, the relationship is not treated as inline link relationship. This is a user property used in active assembly relationships.

FILTER_TYPE_COMMUNITY

public static final int FILTER_TYPE_COMMUNITY
Constant to indicate that the relationship set should NOT be filtered by community. This flag is equivalent to using both FILTER_TYPE_ITEM_COMMUNITY and FILTER_TYPE_FOLDER_COMMUNITY. It overrides either of those flags.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

FILTER_TYPE_FOLDER_PERMISSIONS

public static final int FILTER_TYPE_FOLDER_PERMISSIONS
Constant to indicate that the relationship set should NOT be filtered based on the folder permissions

See Also:
Constant Field Values

FILTER_TYPE_ITEM_COMMUNITY

public static final int FILTER_TYPE_ITEM_COMMUNITY
Constant to indicate that the relationship set should NOT be filtered by the item's community. Other objects may still be filtered by community, depending on the other filter type flags. This flag is only meaningful if FILTER_TYPE_COMMUNITY is not present.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

FILTER_TYPE_FOLDER_COMMUNITY

public static final int FILTER_TYPE_FOLDER_COMMUNITY
Constant to indicate that the relationship set should NOT be filtered by the folder's community. Other objects may still be filtered by community, depending on the other filter type flags. This flag is only meaningful if FILTER_TYPE_COMMUNITY is not present.

See Also:

m_name

protected String m_name
The relationship name, server-wide unique. Initialized in ctor, may be modified through calls to setName(String), never null or empty. Note, it is protected so that the same code (of this class) can be reused in the upgrade plugin.

public void setId(int id)
Override PSComponent.setId(int). It sets a valid id, but the id cannot be reset to another one if the object already has a valid id. The id of the relationships are stored in the id/name mapping table, which can only obtained and set by system, not exposed to the public. A new (or next available) id can be obtained from PSGuidHelper.generateNextLong(PSTypeEnum) for a new relationship configuration.

canHaveMultipleOwers

public boolean canHaveMultipleOwers()
Can the dependent of this relationship have mutliple owners. This is a system property by the virtue of the category of the relationship. For example, an item can be related to multiple items via active assembly category of relationships but cannot be related to multiple items (objects) via folder category of relationships.

Returns:
true if the dependent of this relationship can have multiple owners, false otherise.
